Text.SourceString: Yes, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been meaning to meet you. My name is <NPCName>Millie</>.//It’s so exciting to have people moving in.
Have you met everyone?
Should I stop by the dumpster and sort the recyclables, you think?
Nah, not today. Maybe I’ll do it when the recycling center is built.
When we have a community garden, I’ll plant a lot of flowers.//<portrait=annoyed>Won’t be able to help out with gardening except on Thursdays, though.
When we have a community garden, I’ll plant a lot of flowers.//<portrait=annoyed>Won’t be able to help out with gardening except on Thursdays, though.
I like hanging out at work, so I usually stay here until I get sleepy.
I’d rather spend my time at the library than at the house. I mean, why wouldn’t I?
We have a large selection of books here. Feel free to browse around.
This is the perfect job for me. It lets me catch up with my reading in between organizing.
Hmmm… I think I’ll go to the forest to gather fresh fruit on Thursday.
Oh! Or maybe I’ll go to the beach instead! Pack a lunch, bring some books, and soak up some sun.//<portrait=normal>Mmm…decisions, decisions.
I’m grateful for all the donations the library receives. Not just books, you know. We get plenty of money as well.//Some donations even come in from neighboring islands.
Biology has always interested me, especially wildlife.
This is the perfect job for me. It lets me catch up with my reading in between organizing.
I take Thursdays off.//I'll be at the library first thing tomorrow morning.
It turns out I’m not a big fan of the beach…//<portrait=normal>I like to admire it from afar, preferably with a cold drink in hand.
Oh gosh… Sometimes I read too long. Then I get that dizzy feeling when I stand up… Do you know what I’m talking about?//<portrait=concerned>Good thing my housemate is a doctor.
No, she doesn’t give me a discount at the clinic.
How’s life at the farm, you adventurous sword-toting eagle?
I help the mayor as much as I can with festivals, fairs, and such.//Still, I wish I could do more for the town…
<NPCName>Randy</> asked me to collect some articles for the kids. Additional reading and such.
First editions are incredibly valuable! Well, to me, anyway. Generally, that’s where the author’s original ideas shine the brightest…alongside its typos.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh!
Think about it. The very first version of a book that greets the world.
<NPCName>Scott</> doesn’t work on weekends.//Honestly, I don’t think he needs to!
We have the museum under control.
<NPCName>Scott</> doesn’t work on weekends.//Honestly, I don’t think he needs to!
We have the museum under control.
Oh gosh… Sometimes I read too long. Then I get that dizzy feeling when I stand up… Do you know what I’m talking about?//<portrait=concerned>Good thing my housemate is a doctor.
No, she doesn’t give me a discount at the clinic.
My favorite genre has to be romance. The good ones can really draw you in emotionally.
I love worn-out books. To me, they speak of love and appreciation.
That’s what books aspire to, right? To be read over and over again, by many people.
So many books and so little time.
I once read that some plants survive two seasons…//That must be very economical for business, I would think. Less money spent on seeds.
If you have anything to donate, please send it over to the museum. We have a donation box there.
Once you donate to the box, I file all the information before we can start the inspection process. As soon as that’s done, <NPCName>Scott</> takes care of the rest.
My favorite genre has to be romance. The good ones can really draw you in emotionally.
I love worn-out books. To me, they speak of love and appreciation.
That’s what books aspire to, right? To be read over and over again, by many people.
I pass by your farm sometimes, and I must say, there’s no better view of the sunrise.
It’s a magnificent piece of land. But it must be quite a lot of work to maintain!
I pass by your farm sometimes, and I must say, there’s no better view of the sunrise.
It’s a magnificent piece of land. But it must be quite a lot of work to maintain!
If you have anything to donate, please send it over to the museum. We have a donation box there.
Once you donate to the box, I file all the information before we can start the inspection process.//As soon as that’s done, <NPCName>Scott</> takes care of the rest.
I manage both the library and museum here in Starlet Town.
What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Are we finally going to discuss “The Tale of Dulcans”?//<portrait=normal>Have you finished reading the series yet?
I might try diving tomorrow! If I don’t lose myself bird-watching, that is.
Time certainly flies when you’re having fun.
I’ve been trying to write one article this whole day.
I can’t think of anything worthwhile to say.//My brain is clogged.
The Cherry Blossom Festival is one of my favorite festivals, for sure.//<portrait=normal>The beautiful trees, the people coming together to cook delicious food… It’s so wholesome.
Are you planting any melons on your farm?//Oh, right! Melon is a Summer crop, isn’t it?
Every Spring I always think of poor <NPCName>Charles</>. He’s always sneezing as soon as the pollen goes airborne.
I’m starting to see a lot more lizards out and about. Even my lizard, Tin, is a lot more active now.
Tin likes to be out and about. He rarely stays inside his little glass room, that one.//An adventurer!
I can feel the air slowly heating up.
Is it too early to start looking for melons at <NPCName>Sam’s</>? Hmm…

Summer can get pretty stuffy.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I live on Garden Lane. It’s so green and lush. Once you open the window – wah… The breeze is amazing!//<portrait=normal>It’s the base camp for bugs, though. I bet you can catch a lot of them there, am I right?

I was thinking about baking my own cookies for my library’s stash. For the kids, obviously.//<portrait=happy>Instead of buying them from <NPCName>Sam’s</>.//<portrait=normal>But in this heat? I don’t think it’s worth the money saved, am I right?
Pufferfish is opening a stand at this year’s Beach Cleanup Festival. *sighs* It’s kind of hard to say no to them.
We ran out of melons yesterday. I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</> still has some…
The grass is looking kind of sad, isn’t it? That lot next to my house looks so dry.//So yellow… Poor things.
I feel like I romanticize Fall a bit too much.//<portrait=blushing>But don’t you agree there’s something beautiful about writing a novel as the leaves fall around you?
I’m always inspired to write more in Fall. I wonder why that is…
I’m craving some ramen right now. Any kind of ramen. Mmm…
I’ve been doing a lot of communication with Beluga Bay, since we’re the one hosting the Harvest Festival.
Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is really itching to win the harvest display this year…and me too!
The Harvest Festival is one of the more complicated festivals to set up, but I always have so much fun during the festival.//<portrait=happy>It feels like a reward for all the hard work!
Until we meet again, sweet, sweet Fall air…
Ah, dear Fall. How I’ve missed you.
Now it’s Winter, I can finally relax a bit.
I’ve been eating too much ramen, but I can’t help myself!//<portrait=happy>I love the soupy goodness during the frigid Winter.
I wonder how many great authors write in the dead of Winter.//It feels like the perfect season for writing. I prefer writing in Fall myself, though.
A steaming cup of coffee or tea, something to write with, the snow fluttering, and the fireplace roaring…//<portrait=blushing>Doesn’t that sound great?
The best thing about having a doctor as a roommate is I can just ask her to do my checkups at home.//<portrait=normal>I still have to pay her, though, which is fair enough.
It’s the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.//I think I’ll bring some vegetables… I’m not sure yet.
I got my flu shot early this year, so I’m all set.
A lot of people get the sniffles this time of year.
Oh, my! Is this the last week of Spring already?
I need to get my Summer reading ready!
I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.
I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.
I wonder if Sam’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.
I hope <NPCName>Sam</> has blueberries. I’m craving some Summer fruit pies!
I love writing and reading...sucker for romance fiction here, but I’ll read anything.//<portrait=normal>I won’t say no to a book.
I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.
I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.
It’s freezing today.
I’m looking forward to Spring.
I’ll miss the snow, though.
Do I do things differently in Winter?//Hmm, good question.
I guess not.//<portrait=normal>I like my life in the library, but I do visit the beach from time to time.
Please be careful with the books here.//Some of them are very old and delicate, so wet hands can damage them.
I plan to get some writing done today. I’m inspired by the rain.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.
Have you noticed the weather channel isn’t always accurate?//It makes it hard to plan my days out.
The weather channel isn’t always accurate.
I hope it stops raining soon.
I don’t feel like going anywhere today.
Excuse me.
Excuse me.
Does it feel like it storms more in Spring?
Because it sure does feel like it to me.
Does it feel like it storms more in Summer?
Or is it just me?
I plan to get some writing done today. I’m inspired by the snow.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.
I wonder if Sam’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.
You can read about fish here. There are plenty of informative books about when to catch them.
Are you looking for a specific book?
The farming books are over there.
Once you donate a certain number of items, you’re welcome to collect your reward.
Don’t you just love the smell of old books?
When we receive a new shipment of books, I like to do the unpacking myself.
We got several donations from <NPCName>Zarah</>.//She worked with us a couple of times to find some lost treasures.
How’s your lizard knowledge, <PlayerName>$player</>? <NPCName>Tin</> hasn’t been showing up much lately.//I’m getting worried.
<NPCName>Tin</> isn’t really a pet, just a very well-behaved lizard that sometimes comes and hangs out with me.
I get here before 10 am almost every day. I like to be punctual.
Some people think that my glasses are fake. They aren't!//<portrait=normal>They are for fashion, sure! But my eyesight can also use a little help.
I can’t "legally operate machinery" without them according to the law.
The lights here are funny. I think the wiring must be old and needs some work.//<portrait=annoyed>Sometimes they go off and on by themselves.
You can see all kind of butterflies and birds from here.
On your way to town, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It feels too cold to go to the beach. I think I’ll go home after this.
Thankfully, it’s nice and warm in here.
I’m here to pick up some fresh fish for dinner.//I’m thinking about cooking fish tacos tonight… Hmmm?
Or I can just buy a premade meal.//It’s much easier, and I know it’ll be good. Guaranteed.
Cooking can be fun. You can get all the fancy gadgets and try out new recipes.
Going diving, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I should go home soon. I need time to make dinner.
I’m cooking fish tonight!
We have a large selection of books here. Take your time browsing!
I’m hoping we get more first-edition books!//<portrait=normal>Book restoration is a hobby of mine.
I tell you, when I see a beat-up first edition in need of care, it makes my week.
How’s your week so far, you elegant butterfly?//<portrait=happy>Good? Good!
Reading truly is a marvel. How else can we connect so intimately with people across time?
Have you read anything interesting lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m always looking for recommendations.
Tomorrow is my recycling day! Scheduling chores helps me remember to do them.
I don’t often sort my recyclables, though.//<portrait=normal>I’ll make a point to do it when the recycling center is built.
I like to start the day slowly with a book and a warm mug of coffee.
I like to start the day slowly with a book and a warm mug of coffee.
Restoring books is a hobby of mine.//Making covers, taking care of old books… Little things like that make my week.
This is the perfect job for me. It lets me catch up with my reading in between organizing.
How is life at the farm, you elegant butterfly?//<portrait=happy>Good? Good!
We have several rows of first editions here. They’re the library’s most precious assets, at least to me.//<portrait=happy>Some are even signed by the author!
My favorite genre is probably romance. The good ones inspire so much emotion that I feel exhausted when it’s over!
Earlier, I spotted some crows near your farm.//I hope you have scarecrows, <PlayerName>$player</>, those birds eat crops, after all.
Oh! I also saw some parrots!
The townsfolk are quite eager to help out around town, especially with changing the seasonal decorations.
Though I must admit, the decorations are my favorite part, too!
This island’s wildlife never ceases to amaze me. So much gorgeous fauna!
I know I talk a lot about birds, but I’m fond of butterflies as well.//<portrait=happy>All lovely winged creatures captivate me!
I have a good life, all things considered.//I want for very little.
The local legends of this island are rather captivating.//You ought to read up on them, if you haven’t already.
I’m sure a lot of our customs will become clearer with them in mind!
Let me know if you ever want a book recommendation.//<portrait=normal>I often suggest books to townsfolk!
Now, what’s a free-roaming butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Have you finished reading <Italic>The Tale of Dulcans</>?//<portrait=normal>I can’t wait to discuss the symbolism with you!
I suppose you know how it feels to yearn for a change of pace.//You left everything behind to come here, after all.
Once in a while, I get invested in a series of novels, only to find that the author hasn’t completed it.
It’s even worse when it seems like the series will never be finished… What do I do then?
Hmm… After giving it some thought, I don’t think I have a favorite bird.//<portrait=normal>I love all birds equally!
Even crows! They get a bad rap, but they’re fascinating, intelligent creatures.
I know they’re a hassle to farmers like you, but please be humane with them.
I’ve spent the whole day grappling with a single article I need to write.
I just can’t find any inspiration. My mind is thoroughly clogged.
I really do think the Starlet Digest has had its run.//You know, the newspaper.
It’s not worth much. Just recaps, news everyone already knows.
<PlayerName>$player</>… Do you think I talk about books too much?
I… Hmm. No, I suppose I don’t. My apologies for bothering you.

Special.SourceString: Maybe a little. Don’t you have more to say?

Text.SourceString: That’s so sweet of you to say! Thank you. I needed to hear that.

Special.SourceString: No. It makes you happy, so it’s not too much.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NPCName>Sam</> has blueberries. I’m craving some Summer pies!
I don’t go to the forest much.//I suppose I’m not much of a hiker.
I prefer to walk on proper roads.//But in your line of work, walking through the dirt seems unavoidable!
Please be careful with the books here. Some of them are very old and very delicate, so wet hands can damage them.
I plan to get some writing done today. The rain inspires me, after all!//So somber, so gloomy.
Do you suppose it storms more in Spring? It seems that way to me.
Though I suppose lightning storms are still more common in Summer…
Do you suppose it storms more in Summer?
I wonder if Sam’s is open today, what with the awful weather.//I’m running out of milk and fruit.
Brrrr! It is simply freezing today.
I must say, I’m looking forward to Spring.
Though I’ll miss the snow…
